            <persname encodinganalog="100" normal="Palmer, Katherine V. W.(Katherine Van Winkle), 1895-">Katherine V. W.
               (Katherine Van Winkle) Palmer, 1895-</persname>
         </origination>
         <physdesc encodinganalog="MARC 300" label="Quantity:"><extent>1.5 cubic feet</extent></physdesc>
         <physdesc label="Forms of Material:">Correspondence, scrapbooks, directories, newsletters,
            clippings, minutes, reports, speeches, memorabilia, and other materials.</physdesc>
         <repository label="Repository:"> Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell
            University Library </repository>
         <abstract label="Abstract:">Bound volume of letters on the retirement of E. Laurence
            Palmer, 1952; scrapbook of letters on the retirement of Katherine V. W. Palmer from the
            Paleontological Research Institution, 1978; scrapbook on Katherine V. W. Palmer's trip
            to Japan, 1974; medal from the Paleontological Society. Also, Sigma Delta Epsilon
            materials, including correspondence, directories, newsletters, clippings, minutes,
            reports, speeches, and a history of Sigma Delta Epsilon, 1921-1971; and four-page
            mimeographed outline of the development of the Nature Study program in the Department of
            Rural Education at Cornell, prepared by Professor E. Laurence Palmer. Also, letter to
            Dr. Palmer from Pvt. T.A. Baker, U.S. Marines, stationed in Nantes, France, Dec. 29,
            1918, describing his experiences in the military service.</abstract>
         <langmaterial label="Language:">Collection material in <language encodinganalog="041" langcode="eng">English</language>
         </langmaterial>
      </did>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Bound volume of letters on the retirement of E. Laurence Palmer, 1952; scrapbook of
            letters on the retirement of Katherine V. W. Palmer from the Paleontological Research
            Institution, 1978; scrapbook on Katherine V. W. Palmer's trip to Japan, 1974; medal from
            the Paleontological Society. Also, Sigma Delta Epsilon materials, including
            correspondence, directories, newsletters, clippings, minutes, reports, speeches, and a
            history of Sigma Delta Epsilon, 1921-1971; and four-page mimeographed outline of the
            development of the Nature Study program in the Department of Rural Education at Cornell,
            prepared by Professor E. Laurence Palmer. Also, letter to Dr. Palmer from Pvt. T.A.
            Baker, U.S. Marines, stationed in Nantes, France, Dec. 29, 1918, describing his
            experiences in the military service.</p>
         <p>Original drawings by W. C. Baker and printing blocks for "Honne: The Spirit of the
            Chehalis, The Indian Interpretation of the Origin of the People and Animals as narrated
            by George Saunders," collected and arranged by Katherine Van Winkle Palmer, with a
            signed copy of the book and printing blocks.</p>
      </scopecontent>
